'''ExifTool''' is a [[free software]] program for reading, writing, and manipulating image, audio, and video [[metadata]]. It is [[Cross-platform#Platform-independent software|platform independent]], available as both a [[Perl]] library and [[Command-line interface|command-line]] application. ExifTool is commonly incorporated into different types of [[digital]] [[workflow]]s and supports many types of metadata including [[Exif]], [[IPTC Information Interchange Model|IPTC]], [[XMP]], [[JFIF]], [[GeoTIFF]], [[ICC Profile]], Photoshop IRB, [[FlashPix]], AFCP and [[ID3]], as well as the manufacturer-specific metadata formats of many [[digital camera]]s.
{{Infobox file format | name = Meta Information Encapsulation | icon = | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | extension = .mie | mime = application/x-mie | type code = | uniform type = | magic = 7e 10 04 xx 30 4d 49 45 or 7e 18 04 xx 30 4d 49 45 | owner = Phil Harvey | released = 2005-11-28 | latest release version = 1.1 | latest release date = 2007-01-21 | genre = [[Metadata]] | container for = any other file format | contained by = | extended from = | extended to = | standard = | url = [http://owl.phy.queensu.ca/~phil/exiftool/TagNames/MIE.html Tag Names] [http://owl.phy.queensu.ca/~phil/exiftool/MIE1.1-20070121.pdf Specification] }}
== Meta Information Encapsulation == ExifTool implements its own open [[metadata]] format. It is designed to encapsulate meta information from many sources, in binary or textual form, and bundle it together with any type of file. It can either be a single file, wrapping existing data, or used as a [[sidecar file]], carrying for example [[Exif]] or [[Extensible Metadata Platform|XMP]] metadata.
== Supported File Types ==
